data.name: textArea.Text
data.value: The baseline is used as a reference to orient where land is relative to water. This is important for assigning the proper sign (positive and negative) to the rate calculations. Imagine standing on the baseline facing in the direction that the arrows point and select right if land is on your right or select left if the land is on your left. Even if your baseline is drawn entirely on land, with land on both the right and left, there will still be a landward direction. Transects will follow a left or right-hand rule to properly report results that indicate negative values as erosion and positive values as accretion. Direction will be based off the starting point of the first baseline segment (ID=1), which can be visualized on the map by toggling “Show Baseline Orientation” in the baseline settings.
